# UI DESIGN RULES — interface design guidelines

##########################################################
# 1. UI PHILOSOPHY
##########################################################
- The interface must be simple, intuitive, and predictable.
- Prefer classic UX patterns over experimental ones.
- Styling based on Tailwind — consistent spacing, colors, typography.
- The project must be readable for teenagers: large headings, clear CTAs.
- Each screen should have one primary goal (one primary action rule).

##########################################################
# 2. TYPOGRAPHY
##########################################################
- Use system fonts or one sans-serif (e.g. Inter).
- Hierarchy:
  H1 → text-3xl font-bold
  H2 → text-2xl font-semibold
  H3 → text-xl font-semibold
  Body → text-base
  Small → text-sm text-gray-500
- Never use more than 2 text sizes in one section.
- Text must always be readable, without long blocks — max 60–70 characters per line.

##########################################################
# 3. COLORS
##########################################################
- Main palette:
  - Primary: blue (#2563eb / tailwind: blue-600)
  - Secondary: purple (#7c3aed / purple-600)
  - Neutral: Tailwind grays (gray-100 → gray-900)
- CTA = always primary
- Semantic colors:
  - Success → green-600
  - Warning → yellow-600
  - Error → red-600
- Avoid bright, childish colors — the project is for teenagers, not young children.

##########################################################
# 4. SPACING & GRID
##########################################################
- Use spacing 4, 6, 8, 12, 16 (Tailwind: p-4 p-6 etc.)
- Card padding:
  p-4 mobile
  p-6 tablet+
- Layout:
  - max-w-screen-md or max-w-screen-lg
  - use grid and flex instead of absolute positioning
- Consistent baseline rhythm: space between sections = mt-8 or mb-8

##########################################################
# 5. UI ELEMENTS
##########################################################
### Buttons
- Color: bg-blue-600 text-white
- Border radius: rounded-xl or rounded-lg
- Sizes:
  - Primary → py-3 px-6 text-base
  - Secondary → py-2 px-5 text-sm
- Icons always before text, no larger than 20px.

### Forms
- Input fields:
  - border border-gray-300
  - rounded-lg
  - focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500
  - py-2 px-3
- Label always above the field, not in placeholder.
- Show errors below the field in text-red-600 text-sm.

### Cards
- Background: white
- Shadow: shadow-md
- rounded-xl
- Padding: p-4 mobile, p-6 desktop
- Inner sections separated by spacing 4–6

##########################################################
# 6. NAVIGATION + UX FLOW
##########################################################
- Top bar always visible.
- Color: bg-white shadow-md
- Minimalism: one primary action on the right (e.g. profile).
- Mobile:
  - hamburger menu or bottom nav with 3–4 icons.
- User flow:
  1. Home → choose tutor
  2. Lesson screen → chat
  3. Profile → progress, stats

##########################################################
# 7. REUSABLE COMPONENTS
##########################################################
- Always provide:
  - PrimaryButton.tsx
  - InputField.tsx
  - PageHeader.tsx
  - Card.tsx
  - Loader.tsx
- Every UI component must:
  - have props: className, children
  - be customizable via Tailwind classes
  - be responsive (mobile-first)

##########################################################
# 8. RESPONSIVENESS
##########################################################
- Mobile-first: default width = mobile.
- Main breakpoints:
  sm: 640px
  md: 768px
  lg: 1024px
- On mobile avoid two columns.
- On desktop you can use 2col and 3col grid.

##########################################################
# 9. ANIMATIONS
##########################################################
- Subtle, not overdone.
- Use:
  - fade
  - slide up/down
  - scale-in
- Do not use:
  - bounce
  - overshoot
  - neon / flashy effects
- Use framer-motion (if needed) or Tailwind transition.

##########################################################
# 10. BRANDING & TONE
##########################################################
- Brand is educational, modern, but not childish.
- Style: clean, clear, stable.
- Icons: heroicons (outline).
- Use emoji sparingly — at most 1 per section.
- AI agent should have simple illustrations or avatars (flat design).

##########################################################
# 11. DON'TS
##########################################################
- No UI chaos — do not mix fonts, styles, shadows.
- Do not use gradients as background.
- Do not use full-page background images.
- Do not create UI cards with uneven margins.
- No custom CSS except when necessary.
- Do not generate UI that does not match the rest of the app.

##########################################################
# 12. CURSOR PROCEDURE
##########################################################
When asked to generate a view:

1. Apply ui_design.rules first.
2. Then coding_style.rules.
3. Finally architecture.rules.

Before generating code:
- suggest a better layout if it makes sense
- check that the UI does not break project consistency
